Description: # Charred
        
        Very simple package with `is_ascii_char`, `is_same_char`, `is_string`, `is_unicode_char` and `repeat_char` methods.
        
        I will probably add more later.
        
        Install package:
        
        ```
        pip install charred
        
        # or pip3
        ```
        
        Usage:
        
        ```
        from charred import is_ascii_char, is_same_char, is_string, is_unicode_char, repeat_char
        
        >>> is_ascii_char('$')
        True
        >>> is_ascii_char('£')
        False
        
        >>> is_same_char('FF')
        True
        >>> is_same_char('FD')
        False
        
        >>> is_string('F')
        True
        >>> is_string(1)
        False
        
        >>> is_unicode_char('£')
        True
        >>> is_unicode_char('F')
        False
        
        >>> repeat_char('F', 6)
        FFFFFF
        ```
        
